<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>hang one’s hat • hang up one’s hat</xh5><p> <i>hang one’s hat—</i>1. settle oneself; take up residence: She’s looking for somewhere to <u>hang her hat</u>, now that her twentyyear marriage has ended. 2. <i>(on)</i> depend upon smb.; rely on a person: Why that’s my preacher. I <u>hang my hat</u> on him every time.</p><p><i>hang up one’s hat—</i>1. retire from a position or a job: Police chief Ron Johnson <u>hung up his hat</u> today after forty years of service. 2. <i>(coll.)</i> die: Old Johnson finally <u>hung up his hat</u>. He’s been sick for a while though.</p> </entry>
